This project includes **Axios** as an HTTP client (optional).

---

## Basic usage (server-side)

```js
import axios from 'axios';

export async function getJoke(req, res, next) {
  try {
    const { data } = await axios.get('https://api.chucknorris.io/jokes/random');
    res.json({ joke: data.value });
  } catch (e) {
    next(e);
  }
}
```

---

## Basic usage (client-side)

```html
<script type="module">
  import axios from 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/axios/dist/axios.min.js';
  const { data } = await axios.get('/api/ping');
  console.log(data);
</script>
```

---

## Tips

* Set a baseURL and timeouts for production.
* Handle errors centrally (interceptors) if you make many API calls.
* For SSR-only apps, prefer server-side Axios.
